    slug: "english-translation-of-sunan-abu-dawud-5-volumes-set",
    description: `English Translation of Sunan Abu Dawud — 5 Volumes Set is the complete English translation of one of the six most authoritative hadith collections in Sunni Islam, originally compiled by Imam Abu Dawud Sulayman ibn al-Ash'ath al-Sijistani (202-275 AH / 817-889 CE). Sunan Abu Dawud is widely regarded as one of the most important hadith references for Islamic jurisprudence, containing over 5,274 narrations that are organized according to the chapters of Islamic law (fiqh), making it an indispensable resource for understanding the legal and practical rulings derived from the sayings, actions, and approvals of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). Imam Abu Dawud spent over twenty years traveling throughout the Muslim world to collect hadith, interviewing hundreds of narrators and evaluating thousands of reports before selecting the narrations that met his rigorous standards of authenticity.

This five-volume English translation makes the complete content of Sunan Abu Dawud accessible to English-speaking Muslims, students of Islamic studies, and researchers who may not be able to read the original Arabic text. The translation follows a faithful approach, rendering the meaning of each hadith into clear, contemporary English while preserving the legal and technical terminology of Islamic jurisprudence. Each hadith is accompanied by its chain of narration (isnad), and the translator has included notes where necessary to explain unfamiliar terms, historical context, or the implications of specific narrations for Islamic legal rulings. The five-volume format allows for comfortable reading and study, with the chapters organized in the traditional fiqh-based arrangement that covers purification (taharah), prayer (salah), fasting (sawm), charity (zakat), pilgrimage (hajj), marriage and divorce, trade and commerce, judicial matters, Jihad, food and drink, clothing and adornment, medicine, and funerals.

The significance of Sunan Abu Dawud lies in Imam Abu Dawud's careful selection methodology. Unlike some other compilers who aimed for comprehensiveness, Abu Dawud was highly selective, including only those narrations that he believed could serve as evidence for legal rulings and omitting those that were redundant, excessively weak, or primarily of historical rather than legal interest. He described his methodology as collecting the hadith that serve as evidence for legal rulings, and his collection has been described by scholars as the most comprehensive book of hadith for fiqh after Sahih al-Bukhari and Sahih Muslim. This English translation set is produced with high-quality binding and paper designed for long-term use, making it suitable for personal libraries, Islamic schools, universities, masjids, and research institutions. It is an essential addition to the library of any English-speaking Muslim who wants to access the primary sources of Islamic law and practice.`,
    metaDescription: "English Translation of Sunan Abu Dawud 5 Vol Set covers 5,274 hadith organized by fiqh. Essential English reference for Islamic legal rulings."
