    slug: "english-translation-of-sunan-an-nasai-6-volumes-set",
    description: `English Translation of Sunan An-Nasai — 6 Volumes Set is the complete English translation of Sunan An-Nasai, one of the six canonical hadith collections (Kutub as-Sittah) of Sunni Islam, originally compiled by Imam Ahmad ibn Shu'ayb an-Nasai (215-303 AH / 830-915 CE). Sunan An-Nasai is distinguished among the major hadith collections for the exceptionally high standards of authenticity maintained by its compiler, who was known for his meticulous approach to hadith criticism and his willingness to omit narrations that other collectors included if he had any doubt about their chain of narration. Many hadith scholars have ranked Sunan An-Nasai as the third most authentic hadith collection after Sahih al-Bukhari and Sahih Muslim, with some even placing it above Sahih Ibn Majah in terms of the overall quality of its narrations.

This six-volume English translation presents the complete text of Sunan An-Nasai, making this important hadith collection accessible to the English-speaking world. The translation renders the Arabic text into clear and precise English prose, maintaining the legal accuracy of the original while ensuring readability for contemporary audiences. Each hadith is presented with its complete chain of narration, and the volumes are organized according to the traditional chapter structure that Imam An-Nasai established, covering all major areas of Islamic practice and law including purification, prayer, the various types of prayers, funerals, zakat, fasting, pilgrimage, marriage, divorce, trade, judicial proceedings, Jihad, food, clothing, medicine, and virtues and merits. The six-volume format provides a comfortable reading experience and allows for detailed study of individual chapters without the burden of handling an excessively large single volume.

Imam An-Nasai's methodology as a hadith compiler was exceptionally rigorous. He was a student of Imam Muslim (the compiler of Sahih Muslim) and inherited his teacher's exacting standards for evaluating narrators and chains of narration. He traveled extensively to collect hadith, visiting major centers of Islamic learning including Makkah, Madinah, Egypt, Syria, Iraq, and Khurasan. His Sunan is particularly noted for including narrations that clarify and supplement the hadith found in Sahih al-Bukhari and Sahih Muslim, making it an essential companion to the two Sahih collections for students of hadith and Islamic law. This English translation set is produced with durable binding and quality paper suitable for regular reference use, making it appropriate for Islamic libraries, educational institutions, and personal collections. It is an invaluable resource for English-speaking students of Islamic knowledge, imams, researchers, and any Muslim who wants to deepen their understanding of the Prophetic traditions in their native language.`,
    metaDescription: "English Translation of Sunan An-Nasai 6 Vol Set. Highly authentic hadith collection covering Islamic practice with rigorous narration standards."
