    slug: "english-translation-of-the-meanings-of-summarized-sahih-al-bukhari",
    description: `English Translation of the Meanings of Summarized Sahih Al-Bukhari is a condensed English rendering of the most authoritative hadith collection in Sunni Islam, Sahih al-Bukhari, originally compiled by Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari (194-256 AH / 810-870 CE). The full Sahih al-Bukhari contains over 7,563 hadith (approximately 2,602 without repetitions) organized across 97 books and 3,450 chapters, and while the complete work is an essential reference for scholars, its massive size can be daunting for general readers, students, and busy Muslims who want to benefit from the wisdom of the hadith without committing to reading the entire multi-volume set. This summarized edition addresses that need by presenting a carefully selected collection of the most important and frequently referenced hadith from Sahih al-Bukhari in a single, manageable volume.

The summarization process for this edition has been carried out by qualified scholars who selected the hadith that are most directly relevant to the daily practice of Islam, covering the essential topics that every Muslim needs to know, including the fundamentals of faith (iman), the pillars of Islam, the detailed rulings of prayer, fasting, zakat, and Hajj, the etiquettes of marriage and family life, the principles of business and trade, the manners and moral character that a Muslim should cultivate, and the descriptions of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) and his companions. The selection retains the hadith that have the most direct practical application to contemporary Muslim life while omitting the more specialized narrations that are primarily of interest to advanced scholars of hadith science or Islamic jurisprudence. Where context is needed to understand a hadith, brief explanatory notes are provided.

The English translation itself follows a clear, contemporary style that makes the meaning of each hadith accessible to readers who may not be familiar with Islamic terminology. Arabic key terms are transliterated and explained when they first appear, and the translation avoids both the excessive literalism that can make hadith translations difficult to understand and the excessive paraphrasing that can distort the precise meaning of the original Arabic. The physical book is designed for comfortable reading and reference, with clear typography, a comprehensive index, and a table of contents that allows readers to quickly locate hadith on specific topics. This summarized edition is particularly valuable for new Muslims who want to learn the basics of their faith from its most authentic source, for Islamic school students who need a manageable hadith reference, and for any Muslim who wants to keep a reliable collection of the most important hadith from Sahih al-Bukhari close at hand for regular reading and reflection. The summarized format makes it practical for daily or weekly reading schedules, allowing readers to systematically work through the most essential Prophetic guidance over time.`,
    metaDescription: "Summarized Sahih Al-Bukhari English translation. Essential hadith in one volume covering faith, worship, manners, and daily Islamic practice."
